#Approach:

Count Subarrays with XOR K – Prefix XOR + HashMap Approach

Is problem me hum prefix XOR use karte hain.
Har index par current prefix XOR nikalte hain.

Agar kisi subarray ka XOR k hona chahiye,
to previous prefix XOR aisa hona chahiye ki:
previousXor ^ currentXor = k
Isse previousXor = currentXor ^ k

Isliye har step par current XOR nikalne ke baad
required XOR = currentXor ^ k calculate karte hain.
Agar ye required XOR pehle map me present hai,
to uski frequency ko answer me add kar dete hain.

HashMap me prefix XOR ki frequency store karte hain.
Starting me 0 ko frequency 1 ke saath store karte hain
taki wo subarrays bhi count ho sakein jo index 0 se start hoti hain.

Time Complexity: O(n)
Space Complexity: O(n)

#Code:

class Solution {
    public int subarraysWithXorK(int[] nums, int k) {
        HashMap<Integer, Integer> map = new HashMap<>();
        int xor = 0;
        int cnt = 0;
        map.put(0,1);
        for(int i=0; i<nums.length; i++){
            xor = xor ^ nums[i];
            int x = xor ^ k;

            cnt += map.getOrDefault(x, 0);

            map.put(xor, map.getOrDefault(xor, 0)+1);
        }
        return cnt;
    }
}
